      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2023-09-19</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2024-08-12T14:33:50Z</updateDate>
        <cdata>
          <text>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Register America to Vote Act of 2023&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This bill provides for the automatic registration of eligible voters.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Specifically, the bill directs each state that has a voter registration requirement for federal elections to automatically register eligible individuals when they turn 18 years of age.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The bill also provides for the automatic registration of individuals through state motor vehicle authorities. Individuals must be provided with an opportunity to opt out of automatic voter registration.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The Election Assistance Commission must make grants to states to implement these automatic voter registration programs.&lt;/p&gt;</text>
        </cdata>
      </summary>
